          <source>Knowledge check</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Knowledge check</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Knowledge check</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Common modernization triggers for applications and infrastructure include:</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Consolidation of data centers, hardware refresh cycles, and a general move away from on-premises systems</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Incorrect.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>These triggers are more often associated with migration than modernization.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>The desire to deliver apps and features faster, address security issues caused by outdated code, and enable new business opportunities</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Correct.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Modernization triggers include wanting to deliver applications and features faster to users and customers, addressing security issues caused by legacy or outdated code, and enabling new business opportunities with innovative applications.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>The need to maintain some apps on-premises, the desire to be an industry disruptor, the need for lift and shift</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="112" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Incorrect.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="113" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>These may factor into the migration or modernization strategy, but they are not modernization triggers.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="114" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>The desire to empower employees, engage customers, optimize operations, and transform products</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="115" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Incorrect.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="116" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>These pillars of digital transformation are not modernization triggers in and of themselves.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="117" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>A financial services company decides to tap into cloud capabilities by moving their application into containers to avoid changing the underlying logic of their code.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="118" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Which modernization strategy does this describe?</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="119" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Rearchitect</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="120" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Incorrect.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="121" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Rearchitecting is a modernization strategy, but it requires changes to an application’s code.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="122" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Rebuild</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="123" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Incorrect.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="124" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>This is not a modernization strategy as it requires rebuilding the app from scratch.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="125" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Rehost</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="126" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Incorrect.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="127" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Rehosting is a migration strategy, not a modernization strategy.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="128" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Refactor</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="129" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Correct.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="130" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Refactoring involves moving an app to containers without changing the underlying logic of the code.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="131" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>What are some of the challenges in today’s business environment that are driving the need for application migration and modernization?</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="132" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>The need for a hybrid solution and the desire to future-proof LOB applications</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="133" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Incorrect.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="134" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>These motivations might fit some organizations, but they are not characteristics of the overall business environment.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="135" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>The opportunity for market disruption and the need to maintain LOB applications on-premises</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="136" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Incorrect.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="137" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>These are not challenges in today’s environment.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="138" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>The speed of change and the need to maintain competitive advantage</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="139" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Correct.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="140" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>In this digital era, keeping up with the speed of change in the business world is challenging as organizations push digital innovation beyond experimentation to drive competitive advantage.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="141" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>The changing political climate and the need to protect intellectual property from theft</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="142" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Incorrect.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="143" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>These are not trends in the business environment that are driving migration and modernization.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="144" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>What is the first step that should be undertaken by an organization that has decided to move to the cloud?</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="145" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Rehost existing applications using IaaS</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="146" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Incorrect.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="147" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>While rehosting may be the best strategy for some applications, it may not be appropriate for all applications in an organization’s portfolio.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="148" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Move to a DevOps approach</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="149" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Incorrect.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="150" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>To take full advantage of cloud benefits, a DevOps approach of continuous delivery is essential, but it is not the first step an organization should undertake.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="151" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Convert existing applications to a SaaS (first- or third-party) solution</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="152" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Incorrect.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="153" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Conversion to a SaaS solution may be the best strategy for some applications, it may not be appropriate for all applications in an organization’s portfolio.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="154" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Application Portfolio Assessment</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="155" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>Correct.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="156" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>An Application Portfolio Assessment helps an organization better understand its existing application environment.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="157" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>The key focus of the assessment is an understanding of an application's business value and technical characteristics.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="158" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" uid="learn-wwl.app-and-infra-migration-and-modernization.8-knowledge-check">
          <source>These two dimensions will help define both the modernization technique to be used and the potential value to the business associated with the change.</source>
        </trans-unit></group></body></file></xliff>